<br>
&quot;Just one more thing... name's Deuce.&quot;<br>
<br>
He looked at her quizzically. She grinned and replied, &quot;Liz.&quot;<br>
<br>
He tucked his chin to his chest as they headed back through the doorway to join the others.<br>
<br>
He squinted into the dark room, and found the hippie leaning against the far wall, his hand unconsciously guarding the radio. The two newcomers were huddled up, whispering... or arguing, Deuce couldn't tell. They looked like hell.<br>
<br>
They all stood staring at him and Liz. The tension grew thick.<br>
<br>
With a smirk, Deuce cleared his throat and announced, &quot;Hello, gentlemen. I am the alien prince, and I've come for your women!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uravenofmemory.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenofmemory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/28/01 10:57:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> (( Damn damn damn...my job has been kinda hard, and it looks like it's gonna stay that way...I'm still here, but I can't post as often as I thought I was going to. If I don't do anything for more than a few days, just assume that Ed follows along, kay? I also apologize for the extreme brevity of this post...))<br>
