The grizzled man blinked at the new additions to the little party. &quot;Huh...pleezed t'meetcha all, I'm Edward McArthur...nobody in particular, I just saved one of Liz's friends' lives and now I'm here...&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubeige.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beige</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/28/01 12:52:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.livejournal.com/userpic/67453 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> &quot;I'm Dr. Meier. Been looking for... supplies, and stuff - thought we could find something here.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ross nodded. &quot;Just call me Ross. The bridge broke down about ten, fifteen miles from here.&quot; He sneezed violently. &quot;Had a load of fun walking through the storm, let me tell ya.&quot; He took a tissue from his field pack and blew his nose.<br>
<br>
&quot;Anyway, Vick and I were trying to find a woman named Elizabeth Warchol... was a witness to a criminal investigation. Unfortunately, we don't have a picture...&quot; He sneezed again. &quot;Anyway, any help you could give us would be, you know, helpful.&quot;<br>
<br>
The man looked a little surprised. &quot;Um, sorry, I'm not a resident of the area.&quot; His eyes darted from side to side. &quot;There are aliens coming.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, shucks, that's all right...&quot; Ross did a double take. &quot;What did you just say?&quot;<br>
<br>
Before Dr. Meier could respond, Vick stomped back into the room with a sour look on his face. &quot;This's the worst coffee I've ever had in my life.&quot; He paused and proceeded to drink the whole cup. He sighed contentedly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Um... isn't that hot?&quot; Dr. Meier said cautiously.<br>
<br>
Vick clutched his throat all of a sudden and began to make strange noises.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm guessing yes.&quot; Ross said, amused. Vick gave him a dirty look.<br>
<br>
Just then, three more people entered the room. Vick, Ross, and Dr. Meier stared.<br>
<br>
A scruffy-looking man stepped up and announced, &quot;Hello, gentlemen. I am the alien prince, and I've come for your women!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Another nut job...&quot; Ross muttered. Vick blinked. All he saw was a man with a concealed weapon, who had been on their hunting list for years. Rogue agent - his partner must not have noticed. Fat ignorant newbie. <br>
<br>
Vick mulled over that as the others introduced themselves. Fortunately, the gun-toting one... what did he say his name was? Dune, or Droosh, or something. Anyway, he probably didn't know they were Feds. They certainly didn't look like your typical G-men at the moment. He vaguely noticed his partner introducing himself. &quot;Yeah, I'm Ross Powell, and this is Vick. We're with...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;..CorTechs Communications.&quot; Vick interrupted quickly, smiling, willing Dr. Meier and Ross not to say a @#%$ word. &quot;One of our clients lives out in the area, and we were hoping to persuade him to subscribe to our unlimited monthly plan.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ross appeared clueless and confused. Good. Dr. Meier was staring at all the new people in the room. So much the better. This investigation had taken a whole new turn.<br>
<br>
Vick eyed the gun-toting one warily. He was friendly. A bit too friendly. A chill went up his spine as he looked at Vick.<br>
<br>
&quot;You're a quiet one.&quot; He smirked again. &quot;I'm Deuce... with the FBI.&quot; He flashed an FBI ID, and smirked once more. Vick barely noticed the smirk - he was in adrenaline mode.<br>
<br>
Did the rogue still have an ID? Oh, crap. Oh, CRAP.<br>
