<br>
On the doctor's protest, Deuce grumbled, &quot;You lunatic. You don't know what's out there, yet!&quot;<br>
<br>
The salesmen flooded into the hallway behind Deuce. He looked back to make sure they wouldn't get in the way. <br>
<br>
Not in the way... they were just fine... with their pieces out, grabbing wall in standard two by two cover formation.<br>
<br>
Deuce fought back a smirk. Cops or feds. Jesus kissing Mary!<br>
<br>
He gave them a nod, and they crossed the hall in spurts. Deuce took his leg, and rushed the corner of the hall. He didn't have to play by the rules.<br>
<br>
The windows to the front of the police station were lit with fluttering light. Deuce squinted through the dark room. The misting rain outside was aglow with bright light... kind of like a spotlight pointed straight at the window.<br>
<br>
And in that light... shadows were moving.<br>
<br>
Deuce looked back down the hallway at the other three men.<br>
<br>
