Liz couldn't belive what she saw in front of her. In front of the police building sat a large round ship. From the ship human-like creatures had started to emerge. For a moment she had just standed there staring blankly at the sight in front of her. She had no clue what had made her move outside,in fact,she didn't even remeber the trip from within the building to this point. A moment after though she had regained control of her sense and had ducked behind the cornor of the building. The light the ship was giving off was cold and unatural. Liz squinted,trying to make out the figures,but all she could see was the shadowy image of some creature. She could hear some strange noise in the back of her head. It sounded familer to the noises she had heard befor,but the latter has been of a buzzing quiality and this noise seemed more talking sound. It reminded her of that incoharent mumbling one hears when listning to someone far away.Liz looked around for some sort of escape path. Unable to find one,she made herself as small as possible and hugged the wall. <br>
