</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usempaisloan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SempaiSloan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/10/01 6:13:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> The good doctor produced a gadget that looked like a Frankensteined transistor radio geiger counter. Deuce pressed harder against the sheetrock, trying to stay out of the light. The Mod Squad rejects were holding their position, though the fat one looked like he was going to vomit.<br>
<br>
((And I suspect we've discovered Win's secret identity... he's actually Ford Prefect and he's using his electronic thumb to get off the planet before the Vogons wipe it out.  Or...not.))<br>
<br>
Deuce bellowed over the thundering noise to the doctor, &quot;Where's the girl? Where's Liz?&quot;<br>
<br>
He didn't seem to hear. All he did was jam the device into his rucksack and bolted back down the hallway. <br>
<br>
&quot;Hey!&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce kept his position, and let him retreat. The man very well may be certifiable.<br>
<br>
And the Mod Squad were still staring at Deuce.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now what?&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce shook his head. &quot;Fight or flight. Flip a coin?&quot;<br>
<br>
The fat one looked on after the doctor, then scrambled along his knees back down the hallway. His partner called out, &quot;Vick!&quot;, then shrugged.<br>
<br>
Deuce leveled a keen stare. &quot;Go.&quot;<br>
<br>
He got to his feet, but stayed low, keeping his gun forward by his chin. He definitely had training, but he wasn't military... nor was he used to drawing on someone. But Deuce gave him credit... he was keeping cool, even if his gun seemed uncomfortable in his hand.<br>
<br>
As he disappeared past the corner of the hallway, Deuce got to his feet. He stole one more peek at the front doors. <br>
<br>
He froze as a silhouette squared off directly in front of the doors. There was too much light pouring past it through the glass to make out details. It was human-like. Perhaps a bit more willowy. It was tall, and bald... with a child's proportions.<br>
<br>
Deuce was transfixed. He inched out away from his cover, and stood in the middle of the hallway, just staring. It seemed to be staring back.<br>
<br>
Deuce's mind was halted. He felt like everything was slow-motion. It was... euphoric.<br>
<br>
It lifted a hand. Long, spidery fingers extended seemed to wave hello. Deuce felt a compulsion to return the gesture, but something began to eat away at his stomach. He could sense something... wrong. Electricity stabbed up at his feet. The hairs on the back of his neck stood up.<br>
<br>
Deuce shook his head, and dove sideways into the wall as a clap of energy barrelled past his head. His ears were ringing. He kept moving when he hit the floor, and scrambled through a swing gate into a reception desk.<br>
<br>
Alien crapsucker had a weapon!<br>
<br>
His hands trembling with anger, Deuce checked his chamber. Ok, this was war!<br>
<br>
Steadying his feet against the cabinet, he shoved himself upright, and trained his Browning through a glowing hole in the door glass.<br>
<br>
One shot.<br>
<br>
The silhouette fell backwards slowly, almost wilting.<br>
<br>
The hairs on his neck stood up again.<br>
<br>
Swearing sharply, he dove back into the hallway as the reception desk erupted in a tooth rattling fury. Deuce found his feet again, and sprinted down the lineoleum, his gun at arm's length ahead of him. A shadow stepped out from a doorway. <br>
<br>
One of them.<br>
<br>
One more shot.<br>
<br>
He didn't pause to check his mark. <br>
<br>
The suspended ceiling above him blistered, and a bolt of energy pounded down through the floor, missing him by two feet. The heat of the blast soaked through his shoes, and he wondered if he was going deaf.<br>
<br>
As he rounded the last corner of the hallway, he saw the back door, still open.<br>
<br>
And two more aliens.<br>
<br>
He only had time to squeeze of two more shots before he had to duck back. He was pretty sure he missed on both shots. He was getting disoriented.<br>
<br>
Another energy blast perforated the wall beside him.<br>
<br>
Releasing a string of profanities, Deuce tucked and rolled into the open, hosing down the aliens with the last of his clip.<br>
One of them dropped, but the second remained.<br>
<br>
It lifted it hand. Its palm began to glow yellow.<br>
<br>
Electricity lanced across the floor, over Deuce's legs. His nerves were lit up.<br>
<br>
&quot;No. Not now. Not by you!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uzendragonknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ZenDragonKnight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/11/01 11:51:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> ((sorry if this REALLY sucks, I just skimmed through this, looking for the drift of the plot))<br>
<br>
__The young mech pilot walks in slowly, but swiftly looking for work... He looks with happiness as he see's people talking about destroying UFO's..__<br>
*walks over* My name's Ex, people call me that 'cause I've destroyed so much stuff! I'm a mech pilot, you see lookie there, that's my baby *points to his mech*<br>
<br>
__The mech was outsandingly beautiful. One wouldn't really consider it a mech, on ground it looked like a podracer, but one could easily see how it transformed, the back two engines flipped up to create legs, and the wires connecting the cockpit to the engines snapped in wards,allowing the body and the guns to attatch to the &quot;engine legs&quot;. The cockpit flies foward and turns into a regualar mech cockpit__<br>
<br>
*continue's to talk* Ya see, I've got titaniam plastique coverings that are almost invincible, I can blast anything out of the sky! *imitates gun shooting clouds* Whad'ya say??<br>
<br>
*freezes seeing that he wasn't talking to humans...but aliens* WHAT THE F***???<br>
 __the aliens grabbed him by the arms and held him kidnapped, he could already tell what they were going to do, take him captive and try to destroy these infernal humans one by one__<br>
