<br>
They were getting to close. WAY to close. She had to think of a way to get out of here,but she couldn't just run. They would almost certainly catch her. The hsip had landed in front of the police station, possibly the back was still unoccupied? <br>
Befor Liz had time to think about what she was doing,she had darted down the side of the building, trying her best to blend in with the shadow the light created. With every step it seemed as if her heart beat faster and her breath became more and more shallow. She had to get away quickly. There wasn't much time left,sooner or later these alien creatures would come searching for life. If they found her...Liz shuddered. That wasn't something to be thinking about at the moment.  She sped around the corner of the building only to see one of the creatures fall the the ground. There was another one,raising its hand towards the back door,an strange yellow light glowing from the creatures hand...   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/14/01 7:06:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Winlabik jumped out from the shadows and grabbed Liz, making sure to cover her mouth to keep her from screaming.<br>
&quot;Don't worry!&quot; he shouted into her ear, just above the noise from the space craft, &quot;It's me!&quot;<br>
He let go and led her by the hand down the street, they had to find his car, at least, he hoped it would be in the same place. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwinlabik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winlabik</A> at: 8/14/01 7:10:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugothicchaos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gothic chaos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/16/01 7:01:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Liz gasped as Win's hand clamped over her mouth. After she realized who it was,she slowed down her breathing and relaxed. For a moment there,she had thought one of those creatures had creeped up behind her.<br>
&quot;Whats going on?&quot;she shouted to Win. Things had become so confusing. If only she had some clue what was going to happen. But wait,where were they going?And what about the other people inside the building?What would happen to them?<br>
She shouted loud enough to be heard over all the noise,&quot;what are those things?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usempaisloan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SempaiSloan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/16/01 12:12:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 1</span><hr size=1> Final stabs of excruciating pain lanced through Deuce's palms. His ears began to ring, and his head pounded.<br>
<br>
The beast was ready to let it fly.<br>
<br>
Deuce's head went light. Time felt like it was slowing down. His body got light. Light tunneled around his face. He released a drunken snicker.<br>
<br>
So this was death?<br>
<br>
The light dimmed, and he felt space beneath his back. Then the floor.<br>
<br>
His breath pushed out of his mouth with a grunt, and he looked up at the creature.<br>
<br>
Through the noise and confusion, he heard Liz's voice... &quot;What are those things?&quot;<br>
<br>
The creature's head was turned to the back door. It twisted on a high axis in its trunk, and its long, jaundiced arm swiveled.<br>
<br>
Deuce's hand went to his side instinctively. Empty holster.<br>
<br>
He jammed his feet into the floor and tried to push himself back around the corner. The water on the linoleum squeaked loudly, and he didn't get far.<br>
<br>
The creature swiveled back around to face Deuce with an empty, expressionless face.<br>
<br>
It lifted it hand again.<br>
<br>
A dull shot barked from behind Deuce.<br>
<br>
The creature slumped to its knees, black fluid oozing from an entry wound in its head.<br>
<br>
Deuce stretched his neck up.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'll give them one thing... they're easy to kill.&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce let out a breath and chuckled. &quot;Nice shot for a salesman.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You know I'm no salesman. Come on, let's get out of here.&quot;<br>
<br>
He held out a hand, but Deuce pushed up against his knees and steadied himself. &quot;I heard Liz out there.&quot;<br>
<br>
He bolted for the door, peered out into the rain... and paused.<br>
<br>
Deuce glanced back at the alien corpse. He knelt down and turned up its hand. Dead center of the palm was a clear red device... some kind of glass or gem.<br>
<br>
&quot;Come on!&quot;<br>
<br>
Deuce spat over his shoulder, &quot;Hold it!&quot;<br>
<br>
He fished in his pocket for his pocketknife, triggered the small blade, and dug at the rim of the red glass.  Black ooze spread from the lifting edge, and Deuce gave it a tug.  Long conduits pulled from the forearm of the creature, about two feet.<br>
<br>
When Deuce cleared it, he held it out in the rain to get the black blood off. <br>
<br>
&quot;You done?&quot;<br>
<br>
He bundled the conduit and stuffed the mechanism into his coat pocket.<br>
<br>
&quot;Let's find Liz.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=249.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=249.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=249.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showMessageRange?topicID=249.topic&start=81&stop=92>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showPrevMessage?topicID=249.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showNextMessage?topicID=249.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=60><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.emailToFriend?topicID=249.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.threadControl?topicID=249.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=249.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=249.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td